# Marques Bland

## Project Manager Project Management

Phone: **512-475-9411** |
Email: **[mbland@tacc.utexas.edu](mailto:mbland@tacc.utexas.edu)**

Marques is a Project Manager for the Texas Advanced Computing Center (TACC). He joined TACC from the Marquette University in September 2015.

As a member of the Project Management team, he provides support to various projects and groups at TACC.

### Selected Publications

[Use of accounting concepts to study research: return on investment in XSEDE, a US cyberinfrastructure service](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11192-022-04539-8). Scientometrics, 2023.

[Metrics of financial effectiveness: Return On Investment in XSEDE, a national cyberinfrastructure coordination and support organization](https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3491418.3530287). PEARC '22: Practice and Experience in Advanced Research Computing, 2022.

[Best Practices in Project Management in a Large, Distributed Organization: Lessons Learned from XSEDE](https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3311790.3396632). PEARC '20: Practice and Experience in Advanced Research Computing, 2020.

[The Role Cultural Competency Plays in Teaching Data Science](https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3219104.3219160). PEARC '18: Proceedings of the Practice and Experience on Advanced Research Computing, 2018.

[Advanced Computing for Social Change: Educating and Engaging Our Students to Compete in a Changing Workforce](https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3093338.3093391). PEARC '17: Proceedings of the Practice and Experience in Advanced Research Computing 2017 on Sustainability, Success and Impact, 2017.

